---
description: Zephix frontend rules for React and routing
globs:
  - zephix-frontend/**/*
---

Frontend standards
- Role gating uses helpers and constants. No raw string role comparisons.
- VIEWER is Guest. Paid routes are ADMIN and MEMBER only.
- Keep routing stable. Use existing layouts and guards.

Stage 2 (live staging proof) — asset-hash precheck is mandatory
- Before proving any UI state on staging FE, fetch the live main JS asset and confirm it contains the strings under test.
- Record the asset hash (e.g. `index-XXXX.js`) in the Stage 2 report. Prove the hash first; prove the states second.
- A green Stage 2 against a local Vite/proxy or an old live bundle is invalid (OV-1 Phase A: fixture proof in a staging costume).
- Deploy FE from monorepo root only — see `zephix-frontend/DEPLOY.md`.

UX rules
- Do not clone competitors.
- Keep profile actions role aware and minimal.
- Keep navigation consistent with workspace slug routing: /w/:slug/home.
- Portal overlays/popovers/modals to `document.body` (`fixed`, z-50+). Never anchor panels inside table/th cells — see `.cursor/skills/30-frontend-react/SKILL.md` and `ColumnHeaderMenu.tsx`.
